1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper analyzes the impact of network parameters on channel estimation accuracy and spectral efficiency, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper considers a Massive MIMO network and evaluates the impact of network density on spectral efficiency, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper uses a stochastic geometry framework to analyze the network performance, which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper considers the uplink of a Massive MIMO network, which is a technology that can enhance the performance of multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): Although less likely, the paper may also fall under the category of computers and society as it discusses the impact of network density on the performance of wireless communication systems, which can have social implications.
